{
  "texts": [
    "Given the slightly reduced area that VIKING would cover, it was decided also to truncate KiDS to the same total area, which resulted in the final footprint of 1347 tiles.",
    "Observations that were removed after this area truncation are shown in purple in Fig. 3.",
    "Some of the observing time on the VST originally allocated to the now-deprecated KiDS and VIKING tiles was reallocated to observations of deep spectroscopic fields, forming the basis of the 'KiDZ' dataset (Sect. 3.1.2).",
    "A170, page 5 of 54 A second component of the original KiDS survey plan was to re-observe the entire footprint at the end of the survey in the g-band, for proper motion and variability studies.",
    "As the survey progressed, however, it became clear that bright-time was in considerably less demand than dark-time on the VST, with the bright-time i-band observations advancing much faster than those using the dark-time u, g, r filters."
  ]
}